.TH wxSetCursorEvent 3 "wx 2.5.4" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
wxSetCursorEvent \- A \fIwxSetCursorEvent\fR is generated from \fIwxWindow\fR when the mouse cursor is about to be set as a result of mouse motion.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This event gives the application the chance to perform specific mouse cursor processing based on the current position of the mouse within the window. Use \fIsetCursor/2\fR to specify the cursor you want to be displayed.

.PP
See:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwx_misc:setCursor/1\fR

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxWindow:setCursor/2\fR

.RE

.PP
This class is derived, and can use functions, from:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxEvent\fR

.RE

.PP
wxWidgets docs: wxSetCursorEvent

.SS "Events"

.PP
Use \fIwxEvtHandler:connect/3\fR with \fIwxSetCursorEventType\fR to subscribe to events of this type.

.SH DATA TYPES
.LP
.B
\fBwxSetCursor() :: #wxSetCursor{}.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBwxSetCursorEvent() :: wx:wx_object().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBwxSetCursorEventType() :: set_cursor.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBgetCursor(This) -> wxCursor:wxCursor()\fR
\fB                   when This :: wxSetCursorEvent().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns a reference to the cursor specified by this event.


.RE
.B
\fBgetX(This) -> integer() when This :: wxSetCursorEvent().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the X coordinate of the mouse in client coordinates.


.RE
.B
\fBgetY(This) -> integer() when This :: wxSetCursorEvent().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the Y coordinate of the mouse in client coordinates.


.RE
.B
\fBhasCursor(This) -> boolean() when This :: wxSetCursorEvent().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if the cursor specified by this event is a valid cursor.

.PP
Remark: You cannot specify wxNullCursor with this event, as it is not considered a valid cursor.


.RE
.B
\fBsetCursor(This, Cursor) -> ok\fR
\fB                   when\fR
\fB                       This :: wxSetCursorEvent(),\fR
\fB                       Cursor :: wxCursor:wxCursor().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the cursor associated with this event.


.RE
